
 send: generate and send data via UDP.
 It uses different GNU libraries (see --info option)

 usage: ./send -h
        ./send -s 1024 -n 123 -X true -p 1234 -i 10.10.15.1 -w 1234657

 version: v0.3.1
 compilation date: (Aug 26 2019, 08:48:21)

    -s               1024                     size   of udp buffer
    -n               256                      number of frames
    -b               12                       size   of vector buffer (total size is b*s*4 Bytes)
    -c               2                        thread count
    -p               1234                     port where the packets are send on the receiving device
    -i               10.10.15.1               ip address of the receiver
    -w               123456789                waiting time between udp frames
    --help           true                     help (or -h option)
    --info           false                    show compilation options (or -I option)
    --version        false                    show version (or -v option)
